resolution: "ADR decisions all shipped and adopted as standing practice: centralized single-writer finding recording, batched low-risk remediation PRs, settings read cache landed separately (pm-2bn5), pm_health summary default. All 9 deferred findings verified closed; ADR retired from the living log."
expected_result: ADR stays open only until every deferred finding it indexes is confirmed filed as its own item or shipped.
actual_result: "Verified 2026-07-07: all 9 indexed findings are closed and shipped; condition met, ADR closed."
close_reason: "All 9 deferred findings indexed by this ADR (pm-2bn5, pm-e7dn, pm-ul02, pm-vhx6, pm-6l17, pm-jozc, pm-q0kr, pm-oll8, pm-l0jd) verified closed on 2026-07-07 — the stated stay-open condition is met. Decisions (centralized single-writer recording, batched low-risk remediation PRs, deferred settings cache, health summary default) all shipped and remain standing practice."
body: "## ADR record\nContext: full manual review of pm CLI + SDK + ecosystem on 2026-06-07, run with 4 specialized READ-ONLY sub-agents in parallel (code-quality/perf, SDK/extensions/packages, agent-UX/token-efficiency, docs/CI), findings verified in a temp sandbox plus smoke harnesses (dogfood-package-first, smoke:claude-plugin) and the full coverage gate (2559 tests, 100%).\n\nDecision 1 — centralized recording: all agent findings were recorded by the single maintainer session rather than letting sub-agents mutate pm concurrently, to avoid history-drift/reindex races from cross-process writes and to guarantee no duplicate items. This became the standing review protocol (still used by the 2026-07 reviews).\n\nDecision 2 — batched remediation: ship a focused low-risk batch per PR (the first: pm-g799 close-reason never-block, pm-ryik --p alias, MCP/version coherence, docs/CI hardening) instead of one mega-PR.\n\nConsequences: review sessions are serialized through one writer (slower but race-free); finding→item→PR traceability is 1:1; the protocol is reflected in later reviews (2026-07-02 lanes, 2026-07-03 concurrency, 2026-07-04 sweeps).\n\n## Why still open\nKept open while its deferred findings index is verified — close once every finding it indexes is confirmed filed as its own item or shipped (checked during backlog reviews; most have landed via PR#406-#428 era work)."
